### 2. NEW PAGE: Clients (`/clients`) — `src/pages/Clients.tsx`

Nav: roles `['admin', 'sales']`, icon `◉`, label `Clients`, path `/clients`. Add after Campaigns in Layout NAV.

**API additions to `src/api/index.ts`** (append before end of file):
```ts
export interface Client {
  id: number;
  name: string;
  contact: string;
  email: string;
  phone: string;
  industry: string;
}

export const MOCK_CLIENTS: Client[] = [
  { id: 1, name: 'Ford Dealer Group Tampa',   contact: 'Jim Patterson',  email: 'jim@fordtampa.com',      phone: '813-555-0101', industry: 'Automotive' },
  { id: 2, name: 'Metro Health Network',       contact: 'Dr. Lisa Wu',    email: 'lisa@metrohealth.com',   phone: '813-555-0202', industry: 'Healthcare' },
  { id: 3, name: 'Pepsi Regional Southeast',   contact: 'Carlos Reyes',   email: 'creyes@pepsi.com',       phone: '813-555-0303', industry: 'CPG'        },
  { id: 4, name: 'Coastal Credit Union',       contact: 'Amanda Brooks',  email: 'abrooks@coastalcu.com',  phone: '813-555-0404', industry: 'Finance'    },
  { id: 5, name: 'FitCore Gym',                contact: 'Ryan Torres',    email: 'ryan@fitcore.com',       phone: '813-555-0505', industry: 'Fitness'    },
];

export const fetchClients = async (): Promise<Client[]> => {
  try { const res = await api.get('/clients'); return res.data.clients; }
  catch { return MOCK_CLIENTS; }
};

export const createClient = async (data: Partial<Client>): Promise<Client> => {
  const res = await api.post('/clients', data);
  return res.data;
};
```

**Clients page spec:**
- KPI row: Total Clients, Active Campaigns (from MOCK_CAMPAIGNS cross-ref), Total Budget Pipeline
- Table columns: Name, Contact, Email, Phone, Industry, # Campaigns (count from MOCK_CAMPAIGNS by client_id), Spend (sum of confirmed booking rates for that client)
- "+ Add Client" button (admin/sales) → modal with fields: Name*, Contact, Email, Phone, Industry
- No delete (clients have campaigns — soft constraint)
- Row click: expand inline to show their campaigns (filter MOCK_CAMPAIGNS by client_id match; if name matches)

