### 3. UPDATE: Weather page — fleet grid

Current: single unit dropdown + detail view.
New: **fleet grid first, then detail**.

**Layout change:**
- Remove the single `<select>` toolbar
- Render a 3-column responsive grid of compact weather cards ABOVE the detail section
- Each card (`.weather-unit-card`): unit name (truncated), city, large weather emoji (wxIcon), temp `XX°F`, wind `X mph`, install risk badge (`.badge-risk-high/low`)
- Active card: border `2px solid var(--accent)`, elevated shadow
- Click card → set `selectedId`, fetch + show detail below (preserve existing 4-panel detail view)
- Show a "Fleet Risk Summary" bar at top: "X of Y units HIGH install risk" — highlight in error color if any HIGH

**New CSS classes needed in `styles.css`** (append):
```css
.weather-fleet-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 24px; }
.weather-unit-card { background: var(--bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 14px 16px; cursor: pointer; transition: border-color .15s, box-shadow .15s; }
.weather-unit-card:hover { border-color: var(--accent); }
.weather-unit-card.active { border-color: var(--accent); box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(255,107,26,.2); }
.weather-card-top { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: flex-start; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.weather-card-name { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); line-height: 1.3; max-width: 120px; }
.weather-card-city { font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-muted); }
.fleet-risk-bar { padding: 10px 16px; border-radius: var(--radius); margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 500; }
.fleet-risk-bar.has-risk { background: rgba(239,68,68,.12); border: 1px solid var(--error); color: var(--error); }
.fleet-risk-bar.all-clear { background: rgba(34,197,94,.1); border: 1px solid var(--success); color: var(--success); }
```

**Implementation note:** On mount, `fetchInventory()` gives all units. For each unit, DON'T fetch full weather (20 API calls is too slow). Instead, use a batch approach: fetch weather for selected unit only (as before). For the grid cards, use mock quick-data:
```ts
// Mini mock for the fleet cards (real data loads per-unit on selection)
const FLEET_QUICK: Record<number, { temp: number; wind: number; code: number; risk: 'HIGH'|'LOW' }> = {
  1: { temp: 89, wind: 14, code: 1, risk: 'LOW' },
  2: { temp: 88, wind: 18, code: 2, risk: 'LOW' },
  3: { temp: 89, wind: 22, code: 1, risk: 'LOW' },
  4: { temp: 91, wind: 12, code: 0, risk: 'LOW' },
  5: { temp: 87, wind: 28, code: 3, risk: 'HIGH' },   // coastal — wind high
  9: { temp: 90, wind: 15, code: 1, risk: 'LOW' },
  10: { temp: 90, wind: 13, code: 1, risk: 'LOW' },
  11: { temp: 90, wind: 16, code: 1, risk: 'LOW' },
  12: { temp: 88, wind: 11, code: 0, risk: 'LOW' },
  13: { temp: 91, wind: 14, code: 1, risk: 'LOW' },
  14: { temp: 86, wind: 19, code: 2, risk: 'LOW' },
  15: { temp: 85, wind: 32, code: 80, risk: 'HIGH' },  // beach — rain + wind
  16: { temp: 89, wind: 13, code: 1, risk: 'LOW' },
  17: { temp: 87, wind: 17, code: 2, risk: 'LOW' },
  18: { temp: 88, wind: 14, code: 1, risk: 'LOW' },
  19: { temp: 90, wind: 15, code: 0, risk: 'LOW' },
  20: { temp: 86, wind: 16, code: 1, risk: 'LOW' },
};
// For units not in FLEET_QUICK, use { temp: 88, wind: 15, code: 1, risk: 'LOW' }
```

This means the fleet grid is instant (no network wait) and the detail panel loads real live data when a card is clicked. Put a "Live" pill next to the detail section title to indicate it's fetching real data.

