### 6. UPDATE: Layout topbar — notification bell

In `Layout.tsx`, fetch notification counts on mount:
```ts
const [alerts, setAlerts] = useState<{ highRisk: number; pending: number }>({ highRisk: 0, pending: 0 });

useEffect(() => {
  if (!user || user.role === 'client') return;
  // Use mock values (avoid 2 extra API calls on every layout mount)
  setAlerts({ highRisk: 2, pending: bookings-count-mock });
}, [user]);
```

Actually, to keep it real without extra fetches: hard-code `alerts = { highRisk: 2, pending: 3 }` with a comment "// would be fetched from API in production". This is honest and fast.

In topbar HTML (between `topbar-user` and Sign out):
```tsx
<div className="notif-bell" onClick={() => setShowNotif(!showNotif)} title="Alerts">
  🔔
  {(alerts.highRisk + alerts.pending) > 0 && (
    <span className="notif-badge">{alerts.highRisk + alerts.pending}</span>
  )}
  {showNotif && (
    <div className="notif-drawer">
      <div className="notif-title">Alerts</div>
      {alerts.highRisk > 0 && (
        <div className="notif-item notif-high">
          <span>⚠ {alerts.highRisk} units flagged HIGH install risk</span>
        </div>
      )}
      {alerts.pending > 0 && (
        <div className="notif-item notif-warn">
          <span>◎ {alerts.pending} pending booking approvals</span>
        </div>
      )}
    </div>
  )}
</div>
```

CSS to append to `styles.css`:
```css
.notif-bell { position: relative; cursor: pointer; font-size: 16px; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 6px; transition: background .15s; }
.notif-bell:hover { background: var(--bg-elevated); }
.notif-badge { position: absolute; top: 0; right: 0; background: var(--error); color: #fff; border-radius: 99px; font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700; min-width: 16px; height: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; padding: 0 3px; font-family: var(--font-mono); }
.notif-drawer { position: absolute; right: 0; top: 100%; margin-top: 6px; width: 280px; background: var(--bg-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); z-index: 100; padding: 12px; box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.4); }
.notif-title { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 8px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .04em; }
.notif-item { padding: 8px 10px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 6px; }
.notif-high { background: rgba(239,68,68,.12); color: var(--error); border: 1px solid rgba(239,68,68,.25); }
.notif-warn { background: rgba(234,179,8,.1); color: var(--warning); border: 1px solid rgba(234,179,8,.2); }
```

Add `const [showNotif, setShowNotif] = useState(false);` and close-on-outside-click via `useEffect` with `document.addEventListener('click', ...)` — or just toggle on bell click (simpler, sufficient for demo).

