- produced: Gap analysis (7 concrete gaps), full spec for 2 new pages (Analytics, Clients) and 5 page upgrades (Weather fleet grid, Dashboard revenue chart + top units, Bookings timeline/Gantt, Inventory map traffic layer, Layout topbar notifications), exact TypeScript code snippets, new CSS classes, mock data arrays, and no-new-lib implementation approach for the Gantt
- decisions: No backend changes; all new features use existing API endpoints + mock fallbacks; weather fleet grid uses pre-seeded quick-data to avoid 20 simultaneous API calls; notification counts are hard-coded mock for performance; timeline view uses CSS grid only (no new library)
- next needs: demo-builder creates Analytics.tsx + Clients.tsx, edits 8 existing files using Edit (not rewrite), appends CSS, rebuilds Vite, copies dist to public/demos/adverteyes/, confirms no console errors on first paint
- risks: styles.css append must not duplicate existing class names — check before adding; `map-container` needs `position: relative` for legend absolute positioning; weather fleet grid must handle units where `id` not in FLEET_QUICK (default low-risk mock)
